My car was towed on Feb 28 after 10 pm from the Whole foods and Citizens bank parking lot in Brighton. A company called Roberts parking simply took the car to their lot at 25 Goodenough st. 

We did not know where to go until we found the small towing service warning sign in the parking lot with a phone number. They insisted that I come with cash to pay the fine. 

Our gloves and additional jackets were in the car. I was forced to roam around looking for a cab or a ride with my wife and shivering daughter, to go to an unknown parking lot at almost 11 pm in the night.

If I had parked inappropriately for many days or blocked someone or created a safety hazard, I can understand being towed. To be towed from a store parking lot, minutes after we came out of the store, then forced to pay in cash to get our car back, during an exceptionally cold night, this seems criminally negligent! If I parked wrongly, ticket me. But at least leave me a means of transport. What if I had a newborn with me, or a sick elder? What if we were mugged? Or hurt or shot?

Please address this. We cannot have activities like this in a progressive city like Boston.
